.TH "pwm_request" 9 "pwm_request" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pwm_request \- request a PWM device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct pwm_device *" pwm_request
.BI "(int pwm "  ","
.BI "const char *label "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pwm" 12
global PWM device index
.IP "label" 12
PWM device label
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is deprecated, use \fBpwm_get\fP instead.
.SH "RETURN"
A pointer to a PWM device or an \fBERR_PTR\fP-encoded error code on
failure.
